Package org.insightcentre.uld.naisc.constraint

Implementations and interfaces for constraints used in some matching strategies

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ConstraintFactory
    An interface for creating constraints
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bijective
    A constraint of strict bijectivity, that is no element on either side may be linked to more than one element on the other side.
    Bijective.Configuration
    Configuration of bijective constraint.
    Constraint
    A constraint, which both scores the current partial solution, and also decides how a solution may be extended.
    ThresholdConstraint
    Constraint that accepts any solution where values are above a threshold.
    ThresholdConstraint.Configuration
    The configuration for the threshold constraint.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    UnsolvableConstraint
    A constrain could not be solved with the current solver.
